It was two superb weekends of action at the Nairobi Polo Club, Jamhuri Park as the Kenya International Polo tournament came to a close on Sunday.The biggest event in the country s polo calender saw both international and local teams battle it out in captivating matches. In the end, Samsung were crowned the champions.In attendance were Baringo Senator Gideon Moi, executive steward Louise Wood, and businessman Patel Satyan.